%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226b9312f4-c7cf-4918-a427-783ebf2219b4%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20loved%20my%20experience%20at%20Goldman%20Sachs.%20My%20family%20and%20career%20grew%20while%20I%20worked%20there.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20joined%20Goldman%20Sachs%20full-time%20in%202012%2C%20working%20on%20the%20equity%20research%20team.%20Working%20at%20a%20preeminent%20financial%20institution%20like%20Goldman%20is%20a%20dream%20job.%20I%20was%20earning%20a%20good%20salary%20and%20felt%20like%20I'd%20gotten%20somewhere%20in%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20a%20great%20experience%20at%20Goldman.%20There%20was%20a%20flat%20hierarchy%20where%20junior%20employees%20could%20contribute%20at%20the%20highest%20level.%20I%20loved%20working%20in%20different%20locations%2C%20and%20I%20always%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20growing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20long%20tenure%20is%20a%20testament%20to%20how%20much%20I%20enjoyed%20working%20there%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20the%20only%20job%20I've%20had.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20met%20my%20wife%20when%20she%20joined%20the%20company%20in%202014.%20We%20started%20dating%20and%20got%20married%20in%202017.%20Later%20that%20year%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-family-to-florida-for-husbands-job-regrets-divorce-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewe%20both%20relocated%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20Hong%20Kong%20Goldman%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20had%20our%20son%20in%20December%202018%2C%20and%20in%20January%2C%20we%20were%20both%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstrategies-manage-career-get-promoted-from-amazon-vp-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epromoted%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20my%20wife%20from%20analyst%20to%20associate%20and%20myself%20from%20associate%20to%20executive%20director.%20It%20was%20a%20great%20period%3B%20our%20family%20and%20careers%20were%20expanding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225707897b-bff6-4311-ab08-ad9769c75959%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20pandemic%20made%20us%20rethink%20our%20parenting%20arrangements%20and%20I%20eventually%20decided%20to%20quit%20my%20job%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20son%20was%20a%20top%20priority%2C%20but%20we%20were%20both%20working%20hard%20and%20near%20the%20start%20of%20our%20careers%20in%20Hong%20Kong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20wife%20went%20back%20to%20work%20after%20maternity%20leave%2C%20and%20we%20hired%20a%20full-time%20helper%20to%20look%20after%20our%20son.%20We%20tried%20to%20finish%20work%20by%206%20or%207%20p.m.%20and%20drop%20home%20for%20lunch%20whenever%20we%20could.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20hit%2C%20our%20son%20was%20just%20over%20a%20year%20old.%20We%20got%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwfh-fears-impacting-kids-parenting-remote-work-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ework%20from%20home%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20spend%20more%20time%20with%20him%2C%20but%20still%20had%20our%20helper%20around%20most%20of%20the%20time.%20Seeing%20our%20son%20experience%20our%20presence%20made%20us%20realize%20that%20with%20our%20second%20child%2C%20we%20wanted%20at%20least%20one%20parent%20to%20always%20be%20around.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMothers%20typically%20take%20career%20breaks%20to%20be%20with%20their%20kids%2C%20but%20we%20had%20similar%20careers%2C%20and%20I%20was%20open%20to%20taking%20a%20break%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20our%20second%20child%20was%20born%20in%20February%202023%2C%20my%20wife%20had%20moved%20to%20a%20different%20company.%20Goldman%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoldman-sachs-paid-parental-leave-policy-longest-on-wall-street-2019-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eintroduced%2020%20weeks%20off%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20parents%20irrespective%20of%20gender%2C%20and%20we%20both%20took%20parental%20leave.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20reinforced%20our%20decision%20that%20I%20should%20leave%20my%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe'd%20been%20in%20Hong%20Kong%20for%20nearly%20six%20years%2C%20but%20we%20didn't%20want%20to%20build%20our%20lives%20there.%20The%20plan%20was%20for%20me%20to%20quit%2C%20and%20we'd%20move%20to%20Delhi%2C%20where%20my%20wife's%20family%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20wife's%20firm%20was%20flexible%2C%20allowing%20her%20to%20work%20from%20home%20in%20Delhi%20and%20be%20around%20the%20kids.%20Meanwhile%2C%20I%20wanted%20to%20fully%20devote%20my%20time%20to%20family%20rather%20than%20juggling%20a%20job%20and%20parenting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorking%20parents%20claim%20our%20jobs%20are%20just%20a%20salary%2C%20but%20in%20reality%2C%20we%20tie%20our%20identities%20to%20them%20and%20center%20our%20days%20around%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20spend%20eight%20to%2010%20hours%20a%20day%20at%20work.%20We%20may%20have%20a%20couple%20of%20hours%20with%20our%20kids%20at%20home%2C%20but%20they%20aren't%20the%20center%20of%20our%20calendars%2C%20even%20if%20they%20are%20the%20center%20of%20our%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wanted%20to%20change%20that%2C%20so%20I%20handed%20in%20my%20resignation%20in%20November%202023%20and%20left%20the%20company%20in%20February%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20both%20earning%20six%20figures%20in%20USD%20at%20our%20jobs%20and%20had%20enough%20saved%20that%20finances%20wouldn't%20be%20an%20issue%20after%20I%20quit%2C%20especially%20living%20in%20India%2C%20where%20the%20cost%20of%20living%20is%20lower%20than%20Hong%20Kong.%20We%20now%20fund%20our%20lifestyles%20through%20my%20wife's%20income%20and%20the%20returns%20from%20our%20joint%20savings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20very%20privileged%20to%20be%20able%20to%20leave%20my%20job.%20I%20got%20to%20build%20a%20financial%20cushion%20and%20experience%20a%20great%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a98db903-eb0f-4406-b466-3425ea791b3c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI've%20tried%20to%20take%20on%20more%20responsibilities%20at%20home%20and%20relieve%20my%20wife%20of%20them%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20tried%20to%20take%20on%20as%20many%20childcare%20responsibilities%20as%20I%20can.%20Now%2C%20I%20drop%20off%20and%20pick%20up%20my%20son%20and%20care%20for%20our%20younger%20child%20while%20my%20wife%20is%20at%20work.%20We%20split%20tasks%20like%20bath%20times%20and%20putting%20the%20kids%20to%20bed%2050%2F50%2C%20but%20I've%20taken%20more%20ownership%20of%20other%20chores.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20great%20not%20having%20to%20look%20at%20my%20calendar%20for%20anything%20my%20wife%20and%20kids%20need%20me%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20still%20have%20a%20helper%20who%20cooks%2C%20but%20childcare%20is%20handled%20completely%20by%20my%20wife%20and%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20wife%20has%20always%20been%20the%20captain%20of%20the%20household%20tasks.%20Since%20I%20don't%20instinctively%20know%20what%20needs%20to%20be%20done%2C%20she%20delegates%20tasks%20to%20me.%20I%20want%20to%20help%20take%20the%20mental%20load%20off%20of%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe's%20still%20in%20charge%20of%20the%20kitchen%2C%20giving%20instructions%20to%20our%20helper%20and%20cooking%20occasionally%20herself.%20I'm%20not%20into%20cooking%2C%20but%20I%20want%20to%20learn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20now%20probably%20busier%20during%20the%20day%20than%20I%20was%20at%20Goldman.%20I%20also%20have%20side%20ventures%20like%20angel%20investing%20and%20writing%2C%20which%20help%20me%20stay%20intellectually%20stimulated.%20They%20only%20take%20up%20a%20couple%20of%20hours%20when%20my%20family%20is%20asleep.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20want%20to%20keep%20anchoring%20my%20life%20around%20my%20family%2C%20but%20once%20my%20daughter%20starts%20school%2C%20I'll%20need%20to%20fill%20up%20my%20time.%20It's%20more%20likely%20that%20I'll%20work%20on%20a%20passion%20project%20rather%20than%20a%20corporate%20job%20again%20unless%20circumstances%20require%20me%20to%20have%20another%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220f5dba9a-b62f-4303-81a3-36e679cc68d9%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EStay-at-home%20dads%20are%20still%20a%20rarity%2C%20and%20I%20think%20that%20needs%20to%20change%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp