gain%2C%20not%20only%20by%20my%20dad%20but%20also%20by%20my%20brother.%20I%20feel%20he%20should%20share%20the%20money%20since%20just%20the%20two%20of%20us%20are%20left.%20That's%20what%20I%20would've%20done.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20dad%20also%20had%20a%20will%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fhow-does-a-trust-fund-work-basics%5C%22%3Etrust%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20left%20me%20as%20his%20representative%2C%20but%20because%20my%20brother's%20name%20was%20on%20the%20account%2C%20there's%20nothing%20I%20can%20do.%20I%20know%20my%20dad%20caused%20this%20situation%2C%20but%20my%20brother%20doesn't%20have%20to%20handle%20it%20like%20that.%20I%20just%20want%20to%20be%20treated%20equally%20to%20my%20brother.%20What%20should%20I%20do%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESincerely%2C%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELeast%20Favorite%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDear%20Least%20Favorite%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20sorry%20for%20your%20loss%20and%20for%20the%20years%20of%20your%20life%20that%20you%20spent%20feeling%20like%20your%20father's%20%26quot%3Bleast%26quot%3B%20favorite.%20I%20can't%20offer%20you%20any%20legal%20advice%3B%20unless%20he%20said%20otherwise%20in%20his%20will%2C%20the%20money%20in%20your%20father's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fbest-banks%5C%22%3Ebank%20account%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20now%20your%20brother's.%20This%20is%20unfair%20and%20unkind%2C%20and%20you%20have%20every%20right%20to%20feel%20the%20sting%20of%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20being%20mad%20at%20your%20dead%20father%20and%20resentful%20of%20your%20brother%20won't%20give%20you%20the%20life%20you%20deserve%20to%20live%20%E2%80%94%20a%20life%20free%20of%20jealousy%20and%20hurt%20where%20a%20memory%20of%20your%20dad%20doesn't%20ruin%20your%20day%20and%20a%20phone%20call%20from%20your%20brother%20doesn't%20feel%20like%20a%20stab%20to%20the%20heart.%20Escaping%20an%20emotional%20situation%20someone%20else%20put%20you%20in%20is%20never%20easy%2C%20so%20remember%20this%20process%20will%20be%20long%20and%20imperfect.%20Be%20gentle%20with%20yourself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELetting%20go%20of%20old%20wounds%20can%20be%20challenging%2C%20but%20it%20will%20be%20worth%20it%20once%20you're%20on%20the%20other%20side.%20To%20get%20there%2C%20try%20reframing%20your%20perspective%20of%20the%20past.%20This%20will%20mean%20empathizing%20with%20your%20brother%20and%20your%20late%20father.%20I%20know%20this%20may%20sound%20unfair%2C%20considering%20they're%20the%20ones%20who%20made%20you%20feel%20left%20out%2C%20unappreciated%2C%20and%20deprioritized%20in%20the%20first%20place%2C%20but%20we%20can't%20limit%20our%20imagination%20to%20only%20our%20experiences.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20am%20the%20third%20of%20six%20siblings.%20I've%20always%20felt%20lost%20in%20my%20family.%20I%20remember%20driving%20seven%20hours%20to%20visit%20my%20family%20one%20weekend%20in%20my%20mid-20s.%20I%20had%20two%20toddlers%20and%20an%20infant%20in%20tow.%20The%20journey%20alone%20was%20a%20whole%20production.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20yet%2C%20once%20we%20arrived%2C%20only%20one%20of%20my%20sisters%20made%20any%20real%20time%20for%20me.%20My%20dad%20spent%20the%20weekend%20clearing%20a%20field%2C%20my%20mom%20had%20social%20obligations%2C%20and%20my%20other%20siblings%20didn't%20even%20bother%20with%20excuses.%20I'd%20given%20them%20plenty%20of%20advance%20notice%2C%20and%20still%2C%20they%20only%20had%20an%20hour%20or%20two%20to%20offer.%20It%20hurt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20spent%20the%20afternoon%20with%20my%20grandparents%2C%20crying%20on%20their%20shoulders.%20My%20grandfather%20listened%20patiently%2C%20looked%20me%20in%20the%20eye%2C%20and%20responded%2C%20%26quot%3BYou're%20one%20of%20six.%26quot%3B%20As%20if%20this%20explained%20everything%20and%20ought%20to%20comfort%20me%20somehow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20it%20didn't%2C%20but%20years%20later%2C%20I%20understand%20what%20he%20was%20trying%20to%20say.%20While%20I%20still%20think%20their%20behavior%20was%20thoughtless%20and%20unkind%2C%20I%20realize%20that%20as%20much%20as%20they%20love%20me%2C%20I'm%20just%20another%20part%20of%20their%20lives%20they%20had%20to%20try%20and%20make%20work%2C%20and%20they%20had%20their%20own%20version%20of%20the%20story%20in%20which%20their%20behavior%20was%20perfectly%20justified.%20As%20someone%20who%2C%20like%20everyone%20else%20on%20the%20planet%2C%20also%20tells%20myself%20stories%20to%20explain%20and%20justify%20every%20good%20and%20bad%20choice%20I%20make%2C%20recognizing%20the%20humanity%20behind%20my%20family's%20poor%20decisions%20helped%20me%20understand%20it%20wasn't%20a%20personal%20snub.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20dad%20likely%20felt%20like%20he%20had%20to%20clear%20the%20land%20before%20the%20ground%20froze%2C%20and%20my%20mom%20probably%20made%20a%20commitment%20without%20realizing%20the%20date%20and%20didn't%20want%20to%20flake%20out%20on%20her%20friends.%20Their%20behavior%20demonstrated%20poor%20time%20management%20and%20shoddy%20social%20skills%2C%20but%20it%20didn't%20mean%20that%20they%20wanted%20me%20to%20feel%20rejected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20reframing%20makes%20the%20insult%20of%20that%20weekend%20much%20easier%20to%20forgive%2C%20and%20thus%2C%20I%20don't%20have%20to%20carry%20around%20a%20story%20in%20my%20heart%20about%20my%20parents%20avoiding%20my%20company%20out%20of%20sheer%20dislike.%20Their%20mistakes%20are%20about%20their%20faults%2C%20not%20mine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYour%20dad%20treated%20your%20brother%20like%20his%20favorite%20all%20your%20life%2C%20but%20that%20doesn't%20mean%20he%20loved%20him%20more%20than%20you.%20Maybe%20he%20and%20your%20brother%20shared%20more%20interests%20and%20your%20dad%20was%20too%20lazy%20to%20try%20new%20things.%20Maybe%20your%20dad%20felt%20bad%20for%20your%20brother%20because%20he%20always%20secretly%20felt%20you%20had%20more%20promise.%20Maybe%20something%20hap