3A1723360820000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-112440694%2Cimgsize-34412.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Ftechnology%2Ftech-news%2Fapple-ceo-tim-cook-on-former-youtube-ceo-susan-wojcicki-death-she-was-one-of-silicon-valleys-visionaries%2Farticleshow%2F112440692.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Susan%20Wojcicki%2C%20former%20YouTube%20CEO%2C%20passed%20away%20at%2056.%20Her%20husband%2C%20Dennis%20Troper%2C%20announced%20the%20news%2C%20and%20tech%20leaders%20like%20Google%E2%80%99s%20Sundar%20Pichai%20and%20Apple%E2%80%99s%20Tim%20Cook%20paid%20tributes.%20Wojcicki%20was%20pivotal%20in%20Google's%20early%20success%20and%20led%20YouTube's%20growth.%20Pichai%20highlighted%20her%20kindness%20and%20role%20in%20the%20company%E2%80%99s%20history.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20TECH%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Ftechnology%2Ftech-news%2Fapple-ceo-tim-cook-on-former-youtube-ceo-susan-wojcicki-death-she-was-one-of-silicon-valleys-visionaries%2Farticleshow%2F112440692.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Sent%20Money%20To%20Wrong%20UPI%20ID%3F%20Here's%20How%20You%20Can%20Recover%20It%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20ransomware%20attack%20on%20C-Edge%20Technologies%2C%20a%20key%20tech%20service%20provider%20for%20small%20banks%20in%20India%2C%20has%20brought%20attention%20to%20the%20importance%20of%20double-checking%20UPI%20IDs%20before%20making%20transactions.%20The%20attack%20which%20occurred%20a%20week%20ago%2C%20temporarily%20halted%20payment%20systems%20across%20nearly%20300%20local%20banks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20may%20find%20themselves%20in%20a%20situation%20where%20they%20have%20accidentally%20sent%20money%20to%20a%20wrong%20unified%20payment%20interface%20(UPI)%20ID.%20This%20can%20occur%20when%20a%20phone%20number%20linked%20to%20a%20UPI%20ID%20is%20reassigned%20to%20a%20new%20individual%2C%20causing%20unintended%20recipients%20to%20receive%20funds.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20to%20recover%20money%20sent%20to%20wrong%20UPI%20ID%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Col%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EReach%20out%20to%20the%20payment%20system%20used%20(Google%20Pay%2C%20PhonePe%20or%20Paytm)%20and%20lodge%20a%20complaint.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EVisit%20the%20National%20Payments%20Corporation%20of%20India%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnpci.org.in%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20(NPCI)%20website%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20fill%20out%20the%20online%20form%20under%20the%20%E2%80%98Dispute%20Redressal%20Mechanism'%20section.%20Provide%20required%20details%2C%20including%20transaction%20ID%2C%20virtual%20payment%20address%2C%20amount%20transferred%2C%20date%20of%20transaction%2C%20email%20ID%20and%20mobile%20number.%20Upload%20your%20bank%20statement%20showing%20the%20deduction.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EChoose%20%E2%80%98Incorrectly%20transferred%20to%20another%20account'%20as%20the%20reason%20for%20your%20complaint.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIf%20the%20complaint%20remains%20unresolved%2C%20escalate%20the%20issue%20in%20the%20following%20order%20%E2%80%93%20first%2C%20to%20the%20TPAP%20(Third-Party%20Application%20Provider)%3B%20then%2C%20to%20the%20PSP%20Bank%20(Payment%20Service%20Provider%20Bank)%3B%20followed%20by%20the%20bank%20where%20the%20end-user%20customer%20maintains%20their%20account%3B%20and%20finally%2C%20to%20the%20NPCI.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIf%20the%20issue%20remains%20unresolved%20after%20one%20month%20or%20you're%20dissatisfied%20with%20the%20response%2C%20approach%20the%20RBI%20independent%20official%20(Ombudsman)%20for%20Digital%20Transactions.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EFile%20complaints%20in%20the%20jurisdiction%20where%20the%20system%20participant's%20branch%20or%20office%20is%20located%2C%20or%20where%20the%20customer's%20address%20is%20registered%20for%20centralised%20operations.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20retrieve%20money%20transferred%20to%20an%20unintended%20individual%2C%20you%20must%20prove%20that%20the%20funds%20were%20sent%20unintentionally.%20Once%20proven%2C%20the%20bank%20is%20responsible%20for%20reversing%20the%20transaction.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Abhay%20Chattopadhyay%2C%20Partner%20at%20Economic%20Laws%20Practice%2C%20%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20event%20transfer%20of%20funds%20being%20made%20to%20a%20wrong%20recipient%2C%20sufficient%20proof%20is%20required%20to%20be%20furnished%20by%20the%20affected%20user%20before%20the%20bank%20that%20a%20transaction%20was%20done%20incorrectly%20%2F%20inadvertently.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Chattopadhyay%20also%20stated%20that%20if%20the%20bank%20fails%20to%20ensure%20the%20reversal%20of%20the%20transaction%2C%20you%20can%20file%20a%20complaint%20with%20the%20Ombudsman%20under%20Regulation%208%20of%20the%20RBI's%20Ombudsman%20Scheme%20for%20Digital%20Transactions%2C%202019%2C%20as%20per%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fwealth%2Fsave%2Ftransferred-money-to-wrong-upi-linked-mobile-number-heres-how-you-can-get-it-back%2Farticleshow%2F107629883.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEconomics%20Times.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1723360500000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-01%2Fftl8t35g_upi-generic_625x300_12_January_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fbusiness-news%2Fsent-money-to-wrong-upi-id-heres-how-you-can-recover-it-6312585%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22To%20retrieve%20money%20transferred%20to%20an%20unintended%20individual%2C%20you%20must%20prove%20that%20the%20funds%20were%20sent%20unintentionally.%20Once%20proven%2C%20the%20bank%20is%20responsible%20for%20reversing%20the%20transaction.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fbusiness-news%2Fsent-money-to-wrong-upi-id-heres-how-you-can-recover-it-6312585%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%