80%99s%20doubles%20and%20women%E2%80%99s%20team%20events.%20That%20same%20year%2C%20she%20qualified%20for%20the%20Rio%20Olympics%20but%20was%20defeated%20in%20the%20first%20round.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EManika%E2%80%99s%20most%20significant%20achievement%20came%20at%20the%202018%20Commonwealth%20Games%20in%20Gold%20Coast%2C%20Australia%2C%20where%20she%20led%20India%20to%20a%20historic%20gold%20medal%20in%20the%20women%E2%80%99s%20team%20event%2C%20defeating%20the%20dominant%20Singapore%20team.%20She%20also%20won%20India%E2%80%99s%20first-ever%20silver%20medal%20in%20women%E2%80%99s%20doubles%20and%20claimed%20a%20monumental%20gold%20in%20the%20singles%20event%2C%20bringing%20home%20four%20medals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202018%2C%20she%20was%20honoured%20with%20the%20Arjuna%20Award%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20second-highest%20sporting%20honour.%20Two%20years%20later%2C%20in%202020%2C%20she%20achieved%20the%20pinnacle%20of%20national%20sports%20recognition%20by%20receiving%20the%20Khel%20Ratna%2C%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20highest%20sporting%20honour.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20subsequent%20years%2C%20Manika%20continued%20her%20success%2C%20winning%20team%20gold%20at%20the%202019%20Commonwealth%20Table%20Tennis%20Championships.%20Her%20achievement%20of%20becoming%20the%20first%20paddler%20to%20reach%20round%20of%2016%20surpasses%20her%20previous%20record%20at%20the%20Tokyo%20Olympics%2C%20where%20she%20became%20the%20first%20Indian%20women%E2%80%99s%20table%20tennis%20player%20to%20reach%20the%20round%20of%2032%20in%20singles.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20same%20Tokyo%20Games%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F293449%2Fsharath-kamal-table-tennis-player-at-men-single-commonwealth-games-father-dream%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAchanta%20Sharath%20Kamal%20had%20also%20reached%20the%20round%20of%2032%20in%20the%20men%E2%80%99s%20singles%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20she%20won%20the%20WTT%20Contender%20Budapest%20mixed%20doubles%20and%20the%20WTT%20Contender%20Lasko%20women%E2%80%99s%20doubles.%20She%20competed%20in%20the%20inaugural%20WTT%20Grand%20Smash%20event%20in%20Singapore%20in%202022%20and%20achieved%20a%20career-high%20ranking%20of%20world%20number%20four%20in%20women%E2%80%99s%20doubles%20with%20Archana%20Girish%20Kamath.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EManika%20aspires%20to%20do%20for%20table%20tennis%20in%20India%20what%20PV%20Sindhu%20and%20Saina%20Nehwal%20did%20for%20badminton%20in%20the%20country.%20%E2%80%9CLike%20table%20tennis%2C%20badminton%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20so%20famous%20(in%20India)%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Folympics.com%2Fen%2Fathletes%2Fmanika-batra%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EManika%20said%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%E2%80%9CBut%20the%20amount%20of%20recognition%20they%20have%20got%20for%20the%20sport%2C%20I%20would%20also%20like%20to%20take%20table%20tennis%20to%20greater%20heights%20in%20India.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhilst%20table%20tennis%20was%20her%20first%20love%2C%20Manika%20turned%20down%20modelling%20offers%20in%20her%20teens%20to%20concentrate%20on%20the%20sport.%20Her%20dedication%20has%20not%20only%20brought%20her%20personal%20success%20but%20has%20also%20inspired%20a%20generation%20of%20young%20table%20tennis%20players%20in%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHer%20laurels%20indeed%20make%20her%20a%20true%20icon%20of%20Indian%20table%20tennis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Padmashree%20Pande%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1722849309000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D359739%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Khel%20Ratna%20awardee%20Manika%20Batra%20has%20become%20a%20household%20name%20after%20her%20performance%20at%20Paris%20Olympics.%20Here's%20a%20look%20at%20the%20table%20tennis%20player's%2015-year-long%20career.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Khushi%20Arora%22%2C%22engagement%22%